nwName.name: nwName
nwName.description: The name of the NetWare file server.

nwRev.name: nwRev
nwRev.description: The NetWare software revision for this server.

nwRevDate.name: nwRevDate
nwRevDate.description: The release date of the NetWare software revision.

nwConnsInUse.name: nwConnsInUse
nwConnsInUse.description: The current number of connections in use.

nwPeakConnectionsUsed.name: nwPeakConnectionsUsed
nwPeakConnectionsUsed.description: The highest number of connections used since server came up.

nwRevArray.name: nwRevArray
nwRevArray.description: The Revision of the NetWare software displayed in hex.

nwVolTable.name: nwVolTable
nwVolTable.description: The Table containing entries for each volume.

nwVolIndex.name: nwVolIndex
nwVolIndex.description: A unique value for each volume on the server, used to order the list.

nwVolName.name: nwVolName
nwVolName.description: A string containing the name of the volume.

nwVolSectorsPerBlk.name: nwVolSectorsPerBlk
nwVolSectorsPerBlk.description: The number of sectors per block. This is the number of 512-byte sectors contained in each block of the volume.

nwVolStartBlk.name: nwVolStartBlk
nwVolStartBlk.description: The first block available for you to use for data.

nwVolTotalBlks.name: nwVolTotalBlks
nwVolTotalBlks.description: The total number of blocks for this volume.

nwVolAvailBlks.name: nwVolAvailBlks
nwVolAvailBlks.description: The number of available blocks for this volume.

nwVolTotalDirSlots.name: nwVolTotalDirSlots
nwVolTotalDirSlots.description: The total number of directory slots for this volume.

nwVolAvailDirSlots.name: nwVolAvailDirSlots
nwVolAvailDirSlots.description: The number of currently available directory slots for this volume.

nwVolMaxDirSlots.name: nwVolMaxDirSlots
nwVolMaxDirSlots.description: The peak number of directory slots for this volume.

nwVolHashing.name: nwVolHashing
nwVolHashing.description: The flag to indicate whether hashing is in use.

nwVolRemovable.name: nwVolRemovable
nwVolRemovable.description: The flag to indicate if the media is removable.

nwVolMounted.name: nwVolMounted
nwVolMounted.description: The flag to indicate if the volume is mounted.

nwVolPurgeBlks.name: nwVolPurgeBlks
nwVolPurgeBlks.description: The number of blocks waiting to be purged.

nwVolNotPurgeBlks.name: nwVolNotPurgeBlks
nwVolNotPurgeBlks.description: The number of blocks which cannot be purged.

nwIfNumber.name: nwIfNumber
nwIfNumber.description: The number of interfaces for this NetWare file server.

nwIfCfgTable.name: nwIfCfgTable
nwIfCfgTable.description: The Table containing entries for interface configuration information.

nwIfCfgEntry.name: nwIfCfgEntry
nwIfCfgEntry.description: Entry into the interface configuration table.

nwIfCfgSignature.name: nwIfCfgSignature
nwIfCfgSignature.description: The string 'HardwareDriverMLID' followed by 8 spaces is the first entry in the configuration table.

nwIfCfgMajVer.name: nwIfCfgMajVer
nwIfCfgMajVer.description: The current major version number of the configuration table structure.

nwIfCfgMinVer.name: nwIfCfgMinVer
nwIfCfgMinVer.description: The current minor version number of the configuration table structure.(0..99 decimal).

nwIfCfgNodeAddress.name: nwIfCfgNodeAddress
nwIfCfgNodeAddress.description: The node address of the LAN board. An MLID can call ParseDriverParameters to prompt a console operator to configure this address at the command line. Otherwise the MLID can read the hardware to determine a board's node address.

nwIfCfgModeFlags.name: nwIfCfgModeFlags
nwIfCfgModeFlags.description: The mode flags with bit map as follows: bit 0 - set to 1. It indicates if a real driver. bit 1 - set driver uses DMA, bit 2 - reserved for NetWare; must be 0. bit 3 - set if driver supports multicasting, bit 4 - set to 0. bit 5 - set to 0. bit 6 - set if driver supports raw sends. bit 7 - set to 0. Unused bits are reserved and should always be set to 0.

nwIfCfgBoardNo.name: nwIfCfgBoardNo
nwIfCfgBoardNo.description: A unique value for each board in the configuration table used by SNMP to order the list. This corresponds to the logical board number (1- 63) assigned to this LAN board by the Link Support Layer (LSL).

nwIfCfgBoardInst.name: nwIfCfgBoardInst
nwIfCfgBoardInst.description: The (physical) board instance. The number of the physical card that the logical board is using. If your driver is driving one physical card, all the logical boards using this card would put a value 1 in this field. If you load a second physical card, the value 2 would be the board instance.

nwIfCfgMaxDataSz.name: nwIfCfgMaxDataSz
nwIfCfgMaxDataSz.description: The largest possible packet size (in bytes) that can be transmitted and/or received by the LAN board.

nwIfCfgMaxRcvSz.name: nwIfCfgMaxRcvSz
nwIfCfgMaxRcvSz.description: The maximum size (or best receive size) a packet could be.

nwIfCfgRcvSz.name: nwIfCfgRcvSz
nwIfCfgRcvSz.description: The maximum size a protocol stack can send or receive using this board.

nwIfCfgCardName.name: nwIfCfgCardName
nwIfCfgCardName.description: A string containing a name which uniquely identifies the interface card hardware.

nwIfCfgShortName.name: nwIfCfgShortName
nwIfCfgShortName.description: A string describing the LAN board in 8 characters or less.

nwIfCfgMediaType.name: nwIfCfgMediaType
nwIfCfgMediaType.description: A string describing the MLID's frame type. Examples include `ETHERNET_802.3` and `ETHERNET_II`.

nwIfCfgCardId.name: nwIfCfgCardId
nwIfCfgCardId.description: A reserved field. The Independent Manufacture Support Program (IMSP) assigns a number to each make of LAN board and/or drver if the table version is 1.0. This field is reserved if the table version is 1.1.

nwIfCfgMediaId.name: nwIfCfgMediaId
nwIfCfgMediaId.description: This number identifies the link-level envelope used by the MLID. The ID is associated with a FrameType (nwIfCfgMediaType) string and is assigned with the string. A few examples: MediaId FrameTypeString 01 - LocalTalk 02 - Ethernet_II 03 - Ethernet_802.2 04 - TokenRing 05 - 802.3 For more information contact Novell.

nwIfCfgTransportTM.name: nwIfCfgTransportTM
nwIfCfgTransportTM.description: The time (in ticks) it takes the LAN board to transmit a 576 byte packet. This field cannot be 0. Most MLIDs will set this to a value of 1.

nwIfCfgMlidMajVer.name: nwIfCfgMlidMajVer
nwIfCfgMlidMajVer.description: The current revision level of the MLID. It should match the revision level displayed by the MLID.

nwIfCfgMlidMinVer.name: nwIfCfgMlidMinVer
nwIfCfgMlidMinVer.description: The current minor version number of the MLID.

nwIfCfgFlags.name: nwIfCfgFlags
nwIfCfgFlags.description: The bus types of physical cards that the MLID supports. Unused bits must be set to 0. EISA 0001h; set if supports EISA type physical card ISA 0002h; set if supports PC/AT type physical card MCA 0004h; set if supports Micro Channel type physical card. Bits 3 - 7 are set to 0.

nwIfCfgSendRetries.name: nwIfCfgSendRetries
nwIfCfgSendRetries.description: Number of times the MLID should retry send events before aborting the send.

nwIfCfgShareFlags.name: nwIfCfgShareFlags
nwIfCfgShareFlags.description: Bits which inform the system which hardware resources a driver/physical card can share with other driver/physical cards. bit 0 set if LAN board is currently shutdown; bit 1 set if LAN board can share I/O port #1; bit 2 set if LAN board can share I/O port #2; bit 3 set if LAN board can share memory range #1; bit 4 set if LAN board can share memory range #2; bit 5 set if LAN board can share interrupt #1; bit 6 set if LAN board can share interrupt #2; bit 7 set if LAN board can share DMA channel #1; bit 8 set if LAN board can share DMA channel #2; bit 9 set if driver has its own command line info to put in the AUTOEXEC.NCF file. bit 10 set if driver doesn't want any of default info put in the AUTOEXEC.NCF file. bits 11-15 - set to 0.

nwIfCfgSlot.name: nwIfCfgSlot
nwIfCfgSlot.description: If a LAN board is running in Micro Channel or EISA machine, this field holds the slot number where the board is installed. If not used, it should be set to 0.

nwIfCfgIoAddr1.name: nwIfCfgIoAddr1
nwIfCfgIoAddr1.description: The primary I/O address for the interface card. If not used, it should be set to 0.

nwIfCfgIoRange1.name: nwIfCfgIoRange1
nwIfCfgIoRange1.description: The number of I/O ports used at IOAddr1. If not used, it should be set to 0.

nwIfCfgIoAddr2.name: nwIfCfgIoAddr2
nwIfCfgIoAddr2.description: The secondary I/O address for the interface card. If not used, it should be set to 0.

nwIfCfgIoRange2.name: nwIfCfgIoRange2
nwIfCfgIoRange2.description: The number of I/O ports used at IOAddr2. If not used, it should be set to 0.

nwIfCfgMemAddr1.name: nwIfCfgMemAddr1
nwIfCfgMemAddr1.description: The absolute primary memory address used by the LAN board. If not used, this is set to 0.

nwIfCfgMemSize1.name: nwIfCfgMemSize1
nwIfCfgMemSize1.description: The number of paragraphs (16 bytes) the LAN board uses, starting at nwIfCfgMemAddr1. If not used, it is set to 0.

nwIfCfgMemAddr2.name: nwIfCfgMemAddr2
nwIfCfgMemAddr2.description: The absolute secondary memory address used by the LAN board. If not used, this is set to 0.

nwIfCfgMemSize2.name: nwIfCfgMemSize2
nwIfCfgMemSize2.description: The number of paragraphs (16 bytes) the LAN board uses, starting at nwIfCfgMemAddr2. If not used, it is set to 0.

nwIfCfgInt1.name: nwIfCfgInt1
nwIfCfgInt1.description: The primary interrupt vector number. FFh = not used.

nwIfCfgInt2.name: nwIfCfgInt2
nwIfCfgInt2.description: The secondary interrupt vector number. FFh = not used.

nwIfCfgDma1.name: nwIfCfgDma1
nwIfCfgDma1.description: The primary DMA channel used by the LAN board. FFh = not used.

nwIfCfgDma2.name: nwIfCfgDma2
nwIfCfgDma2.description: The secondary DMA channel used by the LAN board. FFh = not used.

nwIfStatsTable.name: nwIfStatsTable
nwIfStatsTable.description: The Table containing MLID module statistics.

nwIfStatsEntry.name: nwIfStatsEntry
nwIfStatsEntry.description: The entry in the table containing MLID module statistics.

nwIfStatsMajVer.name: nwIfStatsMajVer
nwIfStatsMajVer.description: The current major version number of the generic portion of the statistics table. The current major version number is 2 for a Netware v3.1x Server. The number is defined by Novell.

nwIfStatsMinVer.name: nwIfStatsMinVer
nwIfStatsMinVer.description: The current minor version number of the generic portion of the statistics table. The current minor version number is 0 for a Netware v3.1x Server. The number is defined by Novell.

nwIfStatsValidMask.name: nwIfStatsValidMask
nwIfStatsValidMask.description: The bit mask indicating which counters are valid. The first 13 bits (starting with most significant bit) represent fields in this statistics table. The value 0 indicates it is supported, the value 1 indicates it is not supported. The bit/counter correlations are determined by shifting left, as you move down the counters in the table.

nwIfStatsTotalTxPkts.name: nwIfStatsTotalTxPkts
nwIfStatsTotalTxPkts.description: The total number of packets transmitted by this LAN board.

nwIfStatsTotalRxPkts.name: nwIfStatsTotalRxPkts
nwIfStatsTotalRxPkts.description: Total number of incoming packets received by this LAN board.

nwIfStatsNoAvailEcbs.name: nwIfStatsNoAvailEcbs
nwIfStatsNoAvailEcbs.description: Number of incoming packets that were lost because of unavailable ECBs.

nwIfStatsTxTooBigs.name: nwIfStatsTxTooBigs
nwIfStatsTxTooBigs.description: Number of times the send packet was too big for this LAN board to send.

nwIfStatsTxTooSmalls.name: nwIfStatsTxTooSmalls
nwIfStatsTxTooSmalls.description: Number of times the send packet was too small for this LAN board to send.

nwIfStatsRxOverFlows.name: nwIfStatsRxOverFlows
nwIfStatsRxOverFlows.description: Number of times the LAN board's receive buffers overflowed.

nwIfStatsRxTooBigs.name: nwIfStatsRxTooBigs
nwIfStatsRxTooBigs.description: Number of times the LAN board could not receive a packet because the packet was too big.

nwIfStatsRxTooSmalls.name: nwIfStatsRxTooSmalls
nwIfStatsRxTooSmalls.description: Number of times the LAN board could not receive a packet because the packet was too small.

nwIfStatsTxMiscErrs.name: nwIfStatsTxMiscErrs
nwIfStatsTxMiscErrs.description: The number of transmit errors for the LAN board. This is MLID dependent.

nwIfStatsRxMiscErrs.name: nwIfStatsRxMiscErrs
nwIfStatsRxMiscErrs.description: The number of receive errors for the LAN board. This is MLID dependent.

nwIfStatsTxRetrys.name: nwIfStatsTxRetrys
nwIfStatsTxRetrys.description: Number of times the LAN board retried a transmit because of a failure.

nwIfStatsRxChkSumErrs.name: nwIfStatsRxChkSumErrs
nwIfStatsRxChkSumErrs.description: Number of times a checksum error occured for this LAN board.

nwIfStatsBoardNo.name: nwIfStatsBoardNo
nwIfStatsBoardNo.description: A unique value for each board configured, used by SNMP to order the list of interface statistics. This corresponds to the the logical board number (1 - 63) assigned to this LAN board by the Link Support Layer (LSL).

nwIfStatsCustom.name: nwIfStatsCustom
nwIfStatsCustom.description: The total number of custom variables which follow this word.

nwIfCustomStatsTable.name: nwIfCustomStatsTable
nwIfCustomStatsTable.description: The Table containing custom variables. These are custom counters.

nwIfCustomStatsEntry.name: nwIfCustomStatsEntry
nwIfCustomStatsEntry.description: The entry in the table containing custom variables indexed by the board number and index of the custom variables.

nwIfCustomStatsBoardNo.name: nwIfCustomStatsBoardNo
nwIfCustomStatsBoardNo.description: A unique value for each board configured, used by SNMP to order the list of custom statistics. This corresponds to the the logical board number (1 - 63) assigned to this LAN board by the Link Support Layer (LSL).

nwIfCustomStatsIndex.name: nwIfCustomStatsIndex
nwIfCustomStatsIndex.description: A unique value for each custom variable in the table. (There are a total of nwIfCustom variables).

nwIfCustomStatsDescr.name: nwIfCustomStatsDescr
nwIfCustomStatsDescr.description: A descriptive text string for the custom variable/counter.

nwIfCustomStatsValue.name: nwIfCustomStatsValue
nwIfCustomStatsValue.description: The value associated with the custom variable/counter.

nwProtNumber.name: nwProtNumber
nwProtNumber.description: The number of protocols supported by this server.

nwProtCfgTable.name: nwProtCfgTable
nwProtCfgTable.description: The Table containing protocol configuration information.

nwProtCfgEntry.name: nwProtCfgEntry
nwProtCfgEntry.description: The entry in the protocol configuration table.

nwProtCfgProtNo.name: nwProtCfgProtNo
nwProtCfgProtNo.description: A unique value for each protocol configured, used by SNMP to order the list.

nwProtCfgMajVer.name: nwProtCfgMajVer
nwProtCfgMajVer.description: The major version number of the configuration table.

nwProtCfgMinVer.name: nwProtCfgMinVer
nwProtCfgMinVer.description: The minor version number of the configuration table.

nwProtCfgName.name: nwProtCfgName
nwProtCfgName.description: A string used to register the protocol stack with the Link Support Lanyer (LSL). This string cannot have more than 15 characters (not including the length byte or zero terminator) and cannot be 0.

nwProtCfgRegName.name: nwProtCfgRegName
nwProtCfgRegName.description: A string containing the name of the protocol stack. It is a length-preceded, zero-terminated string.

nwProtCfgStkMajVer.name: nwProtCfgStkMajVer
nwProtCfgStkMajVer.description: The major version number of the protocol stack. The number in this field is a decimal number.

nwProtCfgStkMinVer.name: nwProtCfgStkMinVer
nwProtCfgStkMinVer.description: The minor version number of the protocol stack. The number in this field is a decimal number.

nwProtStatsTable.name: nwProtStatsTable
nwProtStatsTable.description: The table containing protocol statistics information.

nwProtStatsEntry.name: nwProtStatsEntry
nwProtStatsEntry.description: The entry in the protocol statistics table indexed by the protocol statistics number.

nwProtStatsProtNo.name: nwProtStatsProtNo
nwProtStatsProtNo.description: A unique value for each protocol supported on the server, used by SNMP to order the list.

nwProtStatsMajVer.name: nwProtStatsMajVer
nwProtStatsMajVer.description: The major version number of the protocol stack statistics table.

nwProtStatsMinVer.name: nwProtStatsMinVer
nwProtStatsMinVer.description: The minor version number of the protocol stack statistics table.

nwProtStatsValidMask.name: nwProtStatsValidMask
nwProtStatsValidMask.description: A bit mask indicating which counters are used. The value 0 indicates Yes; the value 1 indicates No. The bit/counter correlations are determine by shifting left, as you move down the counters in the table.

nwProtStatsTotalTxPkts.name: nwProtStatsTotalTxPkts
nwProtStatsTotalTxPkts.description: The total number of packets that were requested to be transmitted (whether they were actually transmitted or not).

nwProtStatsTotalRxPkts.name: nwProtStatsTotalRxPkts
nwProtStatsTotalRxPkts.description: The total number of incoming packets that were received.

nwProtStatsIgnoredRxPkts.name: nwProtStatsIgnoredRxPkts
nwProtStatsIgnoredRxPkts.description: The total number of incoming packets that were ignored by the stack.

nwProtStatsCustom.name: nwProtStatsCustom
nwProtStatsCustom.description: The total number of custom counters following this field.

nwProtCustomStatsTable.name: nwProtCustomStatsTable
nwProtCustomStatsTable.description: The table of custom statistics for the protocol.

nwProtCustomStatsEntry.name: nwProtCustomStatsEntry
nwProtCustomStatsEntry.description: The entry in table of custom statistics indexed by the protocol number and the index.

nwProtCustomStatsProtNo.name: nwProtCustomStatsProtNo
nwProtCustomStatsProtNo.description: A unique value for each protocol supported, used by SNMP to order the list.

nwProtCustomStatsIndex.name: nwProtCustomStatsIndex
nwProtCustomStatsIndex.description: A unique value for each statistic in the custom statistics table.

nwProtCustomStatsDescr.name: nwProtCustomStatsDescr
nwProtCustomStatsDescr.description: A string describing for the custom statistic.

nwProtCustomStatsValue.name: nwProtCustomStatsValue
nwProtCustomStatsValue.description: The value of the custom statistic.
